rComments: Bodia is especially good with one on one instruction, but she also has the ability to draw individuals, who may have a tendency to hold back, outward into class participation.

The course was an introduction to research and writing in French. Mme. Machariat was very helpful when it came to assignment completion and made herself available when I had questions - even after the semester was over. Albeit the course's concentration on research methods, she gave us the opportunity to learn about postcolonial literature.

Madame MacHaria knows her stuff well, but the class could seem slightly intimidating for those who are not fluent in French. The method of instruction was not always very clear and the grading (i.e. oral quiz) was a bit harsh. Make sure to study everything before quizzes, as the sample assignments do not really prepare you well for real tests.
